1: The Fed continues to keep interest rates unchanged;
2: The Fed's dot plot shows that two interest rate cuts are expected in 2025;
3: Trump will attend the Digital Asset Summit on Thursday and announce his subsequent crypto policy;
4: Fed Chairman Powell: The Fed has made a technical decision to slow down the pace of balance sheet reduction;
5: The probability of the Fed's interest rate cut in June has increased slightly;
6: Fed mouthpiece: Almost all members have seen the risk of economic downturn;
7: Powell mentioned "tariffs" to admit that Trump's policies affect the economy;
8: Fed Chairman Powell: We are at a stage where we can cut interest rates or maintain the current obviously tight policy stance;
9: Hyperliquid 50x leveraged whales eat both long and short during the Fed's interest rate decision, and made a profit of 164% in 3 hours;
10: mubarak, Broccoli (CZ's Dog) and TUT are temporarily ranked in the top three of Binance voting;
11: 10x Research: US inflation concerns eased, Bitcoin is expected to rebound to more than $90,000;
12: Bitwise CIO: Continue to buy Bitcoin during the crisis, and you will usually get higher returns within a year;
13: Ripple CEO: US SEC will give up appealing to Ripple;
14: Standard Chartered: Coinbase "actively sold" 12,652 ETH in Q4 last year;
15: ZachXBT: The X account of the "50x leveraged whale on Hyperliquid" was purchased from others;
16: The 50x leveraged whale on Hyperliquid deleted the tweets and DeBank account confronting ZachXBT;
17: Digital asset wallet provider Utila completed US$18 million in financing, led by Nyca Partners;
18: Decentralized AI service network Pluralis completed US$7.6 million in financing, led by USV and others;
19: Telegram founder: Telegram's monthly active users have exceeded 1 billion, making it the world's second largest messaging application after WeChat;
20: Uniswap The community approved a $165.5 million fund allocation to pave the way for fee conversion; 
21: Kraken plans to acquire futures trading platform NinjaTrader for $1.5 billion.
